    <div class="column-two-thirds">
      
  <p class="gem-c-lead-paragraph ">
    How we take account of Welsh language needs when we provide services to the public in Wales.
  </p>

      
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid-row ">
    <div class="column-two-thirds">
        <div id="contents" class="app-c-contents-list-with-body">
    
        <div class="responsive-bottom-margin">
          
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak " data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<p>In accordance with the provisions of the Welsh Language Act 1993, Companies House provides a service for companies or Limited liability partnerships who wish to <a href="https://www.gov.uk/companies-house-welsh-service">conduct their business in Welsh</a>.</p>

<p>Companies House agreed a revised Welsh language scheme with the Welsh Language Board on 20 April 2010.  This set out how Companies House would deliver services to its customers in Welsh.</p>

<p>We published our latest Welsh language scheme on 19 May 2014.</p>

